                        <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3120Anapho">Anaphora of John Chrysostom</title>
                        <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                           ቅዳሴ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ አፈ፡ ወርቅ፡ ዘቍርባን፡ እይብል፡ ዲያቆን። ላዕለ፡ ይኩን፡ ሕሊናክሙ፡
                        </incipit>
                        <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                           ወምስለ፡ ቅዱስ፡ መንፈስ፡ ስብሐት፡ ወእኂዝ፡ ይእዜኒ፡ ወዘልፈኒ፡ ወለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፨
                        </explicit>
                        <note>The text ends abruptly on <locus target="#4r"/> with the word <q xml:lang="gez">ወለሐዋር<supplied reason="lost">ይቲከ</supplied>
                           </q> 
                           and follows on <locus target="#25v"/> 
                           (cp. <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/TQ2NBVAC"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Dillmann1866Chrestomathia"/><title level="m">Chrestomathia Aethiopica edita et glossario explanata</title><editor><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Christian Friedrich August</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Dillmann</t:surname></editor><pubPlace>Lipsiae</pubPlace><publisher>T. O. Weigel</publisher><date>1866</date><note type="url">https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_V2XoxZmczckC</note><citedRange unit="page">55, l. 10</citedRange></bibl>).
                        </note>
                        
